  <h2>The Opportunity</h2>

  <p>The total investment to build every remaining cancer detection algorithm for routine blood work is less than the cost of treating 125 late-stage cancer patients for a single year. The return is an estimated <strong>100,000 to 175,000 lives saved annually</strong>, using blood tests already drawn and analyzed, with data already sitting in electronic medical records.</p>

  <p>The blood is already telling us. We just need to start listening.</p>

